caption: My FAVORITE pupusas. I've been coming here since I was a kid and no other place has come close when it comes to pupusas. I grew up in this area with my family (my grandparents were immigrants from El salvador at the time) and it's amazing to see that this place is still there. I've had other items on the menu, but I mostly go for the pupusas and horchata.  The service is quick, fast, and the employees are always friendly.

It was well cooked but the flavor of chicharrón/pork and queso was good but wasn’t amazing. Still worth it for how much you get. The plantains were really good and the beans/frijoles had a ton of flavor. It’s a cute homey space inside as well. I’d go again.
